<chapter xml:id="inheritance"
         xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Inheritance</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>So far we have looked at two ways to implement <q>has-a</q> relationships: composition and aggregation. In this chapter, we will examine a new kind of relationship between objects, <q>is-a</q>.</p>
    <p>Is-a relationships in object-oriented programming are established through a technique called <term>inheritance</term>.</p>
  </introduction>

